cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.CL

The paper proposes a method for multi-task learning using dynamic weights for joint loss, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The proposed method is applied to an end-to-end multimodal emotion and gender recognition model using audio and video data, which involves computer vision and multimedia analysis, making "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and "cs.MM" (Multimedia) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the performance of the model in terms of generalizability, which is related to "cs.SD" (Sound and Music Computing) and "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
